zed using x-ray crystallog.", " >> More from SciFinder ", "\u00ae", "https://chemport.cas.org/services/resolver?origin=ACS&resolution=options&coi=1%3ACAS%3A528%3ADC%252BD2cXns12rt7o%253D&md5=e15b88ce9c9529c4166111431d271e1d", "40. ", "Seki", ", ", "K.", " ", "Chem. Commun.", " ", "2001", ",  ", "1496", "\u2013 ", "1497", "[", "Crossref", "], [", "CAS", "]", "40. ", "Design of an adsorbent with an ideal pore structure for methane adsorption using metal complexes", "Seki, Kenji", "Chemical Communications (Cambridge, United Kingdom)", "\r\n        (", "2001", "),\r\n    ", "\r\n        (", "16", "),\r\n    ", "1496-1497", "CODEN:\r\n                ", "CHCOFS", ";\r\n        ISSN:", "1359-7345", ".\r\n    \r\n            (", "Royal Society of Chemistry", ")\r\n        ", "Three-dimensional metal complexes synthesized from Cu dicarboxylates and triethylenediamine (TED), which have an ideal pore size for methane adsorption, have higher methane adsorption capacity than the theor. max. for activated carbons.", " >> More from SciFinder ", "\u00ae", "https://chemport.cas.org/services/resolver?origin=ACS&resolution=options&coi=1%3ACAS%3A528%3ADC%252BD3MXlvVWgurs%253D&md5=cebf42122d6254b07d0f4b25a440c87e", "41. ", "Seki", ", ", "K.", "; ", "Mori", ", ", "W.", " ", "J. Phys. Chem. B", " ", "2002", ",  ", "106", ",  ", "1380", "\u2013 ", "1385", "[", "ACS Full Text ", "], [", "CAS", "]", "41. ", "Syntheses and Characterization of Microporous Coordination Polymers with Open Frameworks", "Seki, K.; Mori, W.", "Journal of Physical Chemistry B", "\r\n        (", "2002", "),\r\n    ", "106", "\r\n        (", "6", "),\r\n    ", "1380-1385", "CODEN:\r\n                ", "JPCBFK", ";\r\n        ISSN:", "1089-5647", ".\r\n    \r\n            (", "American Chemical Society", ")\r\n        ", "The reactions of porous two-dimensional Cu dicarboxylates (Cu fumarate, Cu terephthalate, Cu styrenedicarboxylate, and Cu 4,4'-biphenyldicarboxylate) with triethylenediamine as a pillar ligand yield